actions.text: The House Committee on Rules reported an original measure, H. Rept. 102-534, by Ms. Slaughter.

Rule provides for consideration of the conference report to H.R. 2507. All points of order against the conference report and against its consideration are waived. Debate on the conference report shall continue for not to exceed one hour, equally divided and controlled.
Placed on the House Calendar, Calendar No. 136.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with one hour of debate.
The previous question was ordered without objection.
On agreeing to the resolution Agreed to by the Yeas and Nays: 308 - 100 (Roll no. 146).
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.

official_title: Waiving all points of order against the conference report on the bill (H.R. 2507) to amend the Public Health Service Act to revise and extend the programs of the National Institutes of Health, and for other purposes.

summary.text: Waives points of order against the consideration of the conference report on H.R. 2507 (public health programs).
